<p class="MsoNormal"><strong style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;">Currency<br /> <br /> </strong>There are three separate currencies operating under a Players Membership<strong style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;"></strong></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-left: 18.0pt; text-indent: -18.0pt; mso-list: l15 level1 lfo41;"><span style="mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; color: black;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">1.<span style="font: 7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;"> </span></span></span>Cash &amp; Account Balance</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&ldquo;Account Balance&rdquo; refers to a user&rsquo;s actual cash funds, Â this are eligible for withdrawal provided the relevant aspects of the Terms and Conditions have been satisfied. The Account Balance is funded by deposits (PayPal, credit card, bank account, or BPAY) and also from cash prize winnings.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-left: 18.0pt; text-indent: -18.0pt; mso-list: l23 level1 lfo39; tab-stops: list 18.0pt 36.0pt;"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 11.0pt; line-height: 115%; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">2.<span style="font: 7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;"> </span></span></span>Tournament Dollars</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&ldquo;Tournament Dollars &ldquo;are funds used to enter tournaments on the TopBetta site. Tournament Dollars can be purchased with money from a user&rsquo;s Account Balance. Tournament Dollars may also be granted by the system as part of a promotion or as a reward for referring a friend; as a prize given for a tournament; as a refund given when a user withdraws from a tournament. Tournament Dollars are non-redeemable for cash.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-left: 18.0pt; text-indent: -18.0pt; mso-list: l16 level1 lfo42; tab-stops: list 18.0pt;"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 11.0pt; line-height: 115%; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">3.<span style="font: 7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;"> </span></span></span>Bettabucks</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&ldquo;BettaBucks&rdquo; are the &ldquo;fantasy dollars&rdquo; given when playing in a tournament. Upon entering a tournament, each player will be given an allotment of Bettabucks to play with. Bettabucks are only valid for the tournament in which they&rsquo;re assigned and may not be transferred or withdrawn at any time. Bettabucks are non-redeemable.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 12.0pt;"><strong style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;">Tournaments </strong></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 12.0pt;">A Tournament is a group of predefined races or events. <br /> <br /> A Single Round Tournament is made up of a group of events occurring on the same day at the same venue i.e. a single race meeting.<br /> A Jackpot Tournament is Tournament made up of a number of predefined Single Round Tournaments that are in a sequential in order. Where entry to each stage is achieved by either</p>
<ul style="margin-top: 0cm;" type="disc">
<li class="MsoNormal" style="mso-list: l20 level1 lfo40; tab-stops: list 36.0pt;">Completing      the previous stage and winning an entry to the next stage.</li>
<li class="MsoNormal" style="mso-list: l20 level1 lfo40; tab-stops: list 36.0pt;">Paying      the required entry fee, in either Tournament Dollars or cash.</li>
</ul>
<p class="MsoNormal">To be eligible for the Jackpot, entry to the final stage is required and these terms and conditions must be satisfied.<strong style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;"><br /> <br /> </strong>To enter a Tournament, a Participant must:<strong style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;"> </strong></p>
<ol style="margin-top: 0cm;" type="1">
<li class="MsoNormal" style="mso-list: l29 level1 lfo43; tab-stops: list 36.0pt;">become      a registered member of TopBetta by registering their details via the      on-line registration form on the TopBetta Web Site at <a href="http://www.topbetta.com/">www.topbetta.com</a> and satisfy the      TopBetta Terms and Conditions; </li>
</ol> <ol style="margin-top: 0cm;" type="1">
<li class="MsoNormal" style="mso-list: l17 level1 lfo44; tab-stops: list 36.0pt;">if      the Tournament has an associated fees, pay the required Tournament fees.</li>
</ol>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: .0001pt;"><strong style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;"><br /> </strong>The Entry Fee is quoted into two components (i.e. $50 + $5). Where the larger component is the Prize component referred to as the &lsquo;buy in&rsquo;and the smaller is the Administration component referred to and the &lsquo;entry fee&rsquo;.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: .0001pt;"><br /> On receipt of the Entry fee or on entering a Free Tournament a registered member will be allocated a quantity of Bettabucks (these are fantasy dollars, they have no monetary value and are nonredeemable).</p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: .0001pt;"><br /> One tournament entry per member is permitted.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: .0001pt;"><br /> Bettabucks are for tournament use only, no actual monetary compensation will be distributed. They are only used to determine entrants finishing position in the tournament.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: .0001pt;"><br /> A Member makes a number of bets using their Bettabuck, betting on the races/events that have been allocated to the respective Tournament.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: .0001pt;"><br /> Whilst the broadcast odds for these races are based on live NSWTAB prices, should the member&rsquo;s horse (or dog) place in the race the member will receive the allocated winnings in the form of Bettabucks.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: .0001pt;"><br /> To be eligible to win a Tournament a member must make bets in the respective tournament equivalent to or greater than the initial BettaBucks balance. i.e. if the member received $1,000 of Bettabucks then bets equal to or greater than $1,000 of Bettabucks must be placed.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: .0001pt;">Â </p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: .0001pt;">Members can unregister themselves from any tournament, provided a bet has not been placed and the first race/event has yet to start. A Member will receive a Tournament Dollars credit to the value of their Entry Fee.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: .0001pt;"><br /> Tournaments can be cancelled by the TopBetta at any time and all Entry Fees will be credited (as Tournament Dollars) to the Members.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: .0001pt;"><br /> A Tournament is open until the start time of the last race/event in that tournament<br /> If a tournament has to end before all races have been run (i.e. it gets washed out) the Tournament will be cancelled and all Entry Fees will be credited (as Tournament Dollars) to the Members.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: .0001pt;"><br /> If a particular race/event in a Tournament is postponed (for more than 6 hours from its scheduled start time), or is cancelled. It will no longer be a part of the Tournament and all Bettabuck bets will be refunded. Where a Member has purchased entry to this particular event/race they will be credited the entry fee in Tournament Dollars.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: .0001pt;"><br /> If a Member has bet on a runner and that runner is subsequently scratched, the Member will have their Bettabucks bet refunded. Where a Member has purchased entry to this particular event/race they will not be credited the entry fee but will remain eligible to make additional bets on the race/tournament.<br /> Minimum Prizes are displayed on the Tournament Info page after the start of each competition and will be distributed in accordance with the persons finishing order and the Paid Tournaments Payouts spreadsheet.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: .0001pt;"><br /> In the event that there is a dispute concerning the conduct of a Tournament, the decision of the TopBetta is final and binding and no correspondence will be entered into.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: .0001pt;"><br /> Tournament Prize Winner - The Tournament Winner will be the entrant whose BettaBucks account has accumulated the most BettaBucks throughout the Tournament.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: .0001pt;"><br /> In the event of a tie, the prize will be divided equally between the tying members.<br /> In the event that no winner can be determined for a tournament, the Tournament will be cancelled and Participants will forfeit their entry fee.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: .0001pt;"><br /> This is a game of skill, however the odds of winning the Tournament depend, in part, on the number of contestants and eligible entries received.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: .0001pt;"><br /> Tournament Prize Winner Notification and Acceptance: The Major Tournament Prize Winners will be notified by email, mail and/or telephone and will be announced on or about three (3) business days following the determination of the winner. The Tournament Prize Winners may waive their right to receive the prize and an alternate winner will be selected.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: .0001pt;"><br /> The Tournament Prize is non-assignable and non-transferable. The Tournament Prize Winner is solely responsible for payment of any taxes on the prize(s).</p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: .0001pt;"><br /> All Major Winners will be required to complete and return an affidavit of eligibility and publicity and release of liability form within five (5) days of their receipt of such form. Failure to return the eligibility and release of liability form within five (5) days may result in forfeiture of your prize and your prize will be reallocated.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: .0001pt;"><br /> Reallocation of a prize. Should it be necessary to reallocate a prize,Â the prize will be allocated to the participant with the next highest amount of TopBetta Bucks. In the event of a tie, the prize will be divided equally between the tying members.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: .0001pt;"><br /> Failure to comply with any term or condition of these Terms and Conditions, may, at the sole discretion of the TopBetta, result in the Major Tournament Prize Winner disqualification, the forfeiture of his or her interest in the prize, and the award of the prize to an alternate winner.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: .0001pt;">Â </p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: .0001pt;"><span style="mso-spacerun: yes;"> </span>Acceptance of the prize constitutes permission (except where prohibited) of TopBetta&rsquo;s use of the winners&rsquo; name and likeness for advertising and promotional purposes as TopBetta so determines without notice, limitation or further compensation.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: .0001pt;">Â </p>
<p class="MsoListParagraph" style="margin-top: 0cm; margin-right: 0cm; margin-bottom: .0001pt; margin-left: 18.0pt; mso-add-space: auto; text-indent: -18.0pt; mso-list: l8 level1 lfo45;"><span style="mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">2.<span style="font: 7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;"> </span></span></span>Tournament Prize Pools</p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: .0001pt;">Â </p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-left: 18.0pt;">The Prize Pool for a tournament is the sum of the Prize Component of the Entry Fee for that tournament, this will be the total payout amount on completion of the tournament.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-left: 18.0pt;">Where a tournament is advertising a "guaranteed" minimum prize pool, if sum of the Prize of the Entry Fee is less than the "guaranteed" minimum prize pool, thenÂ "guaranteed" minimum prize pool will be the total payout amount on completion of the tournament.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-left: 18.0pt;">Each Tournament will state a "guaranteed" minimum prize pool.</p>
<p class="MsoListParagraph" style="margin-left: 18.0pt; mso-add-space: auto; text-indent: -18.0pt; mso-list: l8 level1 lfo45;"><span style="mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">3.<span style="font: 7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;"> </span></span></span>Tournament Prize Winners</p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-left: 18.0pt;">Where a Tournament is a single Tournament or the last Tournament in a Jackpot Tournament the winners will receive their winnings as cash and this will be credited to their account balance.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-left: 18.0pt;">Where the Tournament is not a single Tournament or the last Tournament in a Jackpot Tournament and offers a prize as entry to the next stage of a Jackpot Tournament, winners will receive their winnings as Tournament dollars. Where a Member has won entry to the next stage of the Jackpot, the entry fee will be deducted for automatic entry into the next stage. Any other winners will receive their winnings as Tournament Dollars and this will be credited to their Tournament Dollars account.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-left: 18.0pt;">Only one entry per Tournament is allowed.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes;"> </span>Where a Tournament Prize Winner has an existing entry into the next stage Tournament, their winnings will remain in their account asTournament Dollars</p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-left: 18.0pt;">Each Tournament will state the minimum number of eligible prize winners.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-left: 18.0pt;">The number of Tournament Prize Winners is dependent on the number of entrants in the respective tournament.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-left: 18.0pt;">Where the Tournament Prize winner receives a cash prize. The amount a Tournament Prize Winner receives as their cash prize is dependent on the Prize Pool for that Tournament and is a % of the Prize Pool dependent on the ranking of the Tournament Prize Winner.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-left: 18.0pt;">Where the Tournament Prize winner receives an entry into a subsequent Tournament as the prize, the number of entries is dependent on the size of the Prize Pool. The Prize Pool is divided by the the entry fee for the New Tournament with each complete division resulting in an entry being awarded to a Tournament Prize winner. In the advent that there is a surplus remaining in the Prize Pool the next eligible winner receives this surplus in the form of Tournament Dollars</p>
<span style="font-size: 11.0pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: &quot;Calibri&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-fareast-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-bidi; mso-ansi-language: EN-AU; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">The Payouts are defined in the Paid Tournaments Payouts spreadsheet.</span></p>
